No. 4
United States Consulate
Sierra Leone
May 25th 1874

1. Acknowledgement of receipt of dispatches No. 2 and 3
2. Further information as to citizen of Consuate property
3. Suggestionfor settlement by Arbitration

Sir
I have the honor to acknowledge receiptofyoour dispatches No.2 and 3 to which I beg to reply. 

The Consular property has been siezed by Mssn Harris No. for the expenses of the American Consulate only. The amount claimed is exhorbant and they have no agreement or contract ofany kind to show that they are entitled to that amount. Up to the time of thedeparture of the late Consul W. Morgan Esq; Mess Harris No. received all the fees of the Consulate, by private arrangement with the said W. Morgan. They are not therefore entitled toany thing up to August 1st Last. Be pleased to instruct one in this matter.

I should suggest a settlement by arbitration fully beheving such a course practicable. 

I have the remain 
Sir
Your obesdient Servant
Hath Lyon
U.S. Cousul for
Sierra Leone

Honble
C.B.Harris
Assistant Secy
Department of State
Washington U.S.
